The paper deals with the average consensus problem in multi-agent systems, which is a topic in control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY). The algorithms proposed are distributed, which is a common theme in multi-agent systems research (cs.MA). The paper also employs graph-theoretic and nonnegative matrix tools, which are commonly used in distributed computing and network analysis (cs.DC). The eigenvalue perturbation theory is mentioned as playing a crucial role in the convergence analysis, which is a topic in numerical analysis and linear algebra (cs.NA). Finally, the paper proposes algorithms for both synchronous and asynchronous communication, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
